I don't think this relationship necessarily had to do with the issue of control.  At this age, everyone is learning what they can and can't get away with in a relationship.  I don't think that anyone should be dating only one person in a heavy relationship until they have had a chance to explore who they are and what kind of person they need to make them happy.  Some people don't really ever find what they need from someone else because they never are single long enough to find out what is missing from their lives.  I don't think it only has to do with teenage girls, but with everyone who feels unhappy about something, but refuses to actually examine the problem.
